  <summary>8/5/1999--Introduced.
Amends the International Claims Settlement Act of 1949 to grant the Foreign Claims Settlement Commission of the United States the authority to settle claims for damages for American victims of National Socialist (Nazi) persecution. Provides for the judicial review of Commission determinations with respect to such claims.</summary>
